1. Version 0.2

- Review the timeout event on get_esme_session

- Don't like current PDU packing/unpacking mechanism using the pdu_type/1 
  function.

  Consider creating a pack/unpack function for each PDU type. Call the 
  appropriate pack/unpack function by means of the command_id and remove 
  pdu_type/1 function.

- Put the command_id back into the PDU descriptor.

- Automatically add/remove trailing '\0' in C-Octet Strings.

  Pay special attention to C-Octet String parameteres defined as composites
  (records), such us TIME_DOMAIN.  Create a MACRO to assing values to 
  parameters represented as records.

  Cambios en base_syntax.erl

  Modificar la función take_until, ojo con los comentarios que hacen referncia
  a smpp_base: cambiarlos por base_syntax.

  Cambios en los hrls, modificar todos los valores por defecto que incluyen el
  NULL_CHARACTER explícitamente.  El NULL_C_OCTET_STRING es ahora un "".

- Define a couple of MACROS for every composite parameter.  One to assign
  default (record) values, and the other to hide record definition to higher
  layers.

  DEST_TELEMATICS_ID_DEFAULT_VALUE
  DEST_TELEMATICS_ID_VALUE(...)


2. Version 1.0

- Implement a gen_mc_session behavior.

- Implement a gen_mc behavior.


3. Version 2.0

- Implement a gen_re behavior.



